cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SD 

This paper proposes a new model for making predictions in the field of chemistry, specifically in retrosynthesis. The model uses the SMILES representation of molecules and is based on the Transformer architecture. The paper also introduces two novel pre-training methods and incorporates a discrete latent variable model to encourage diversity in the predictions. Given the focus on machine learning and natural language processing techniques, as well as the use of the Transformer architecture, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves training and optimization techniques, which are common in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of SMILES representations and the focus on chemical reactions suggest a possible fit with cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.SD (Software Engineering).
